<p><a name="Further_reading" id="Further_reading"></a></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:152px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Nagasaki_Ground_Zero_C2117.jpg" class="image" title="The black marker indicates &quot;ground zero&quot; of the Nagasaki atomic bomb explosion."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Nagasaki_Ground_Zero_C2117.jpg/150px-Nagasaki_Ground_Zero_C2117.jpg" width="150" height="225" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Nagasaki_Ground_Zero_C2117.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The black marker indicates "ground zero" of the Nagasaki atomic bomb explosion.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>There is an extensive body of literature concerning the bombings, the decision to use the bombs, and the surrender of Japan. The following sources provide a sampling of prominent works on this subject matter.</p>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFThe_Committee_for_the_Compilation_of_Materials_on_Damage_Caused_by_the_Atomic_Bombs_in_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki1981">The Committee for the Compilation of Materials on Damage Caused by the Atomic Bombs in Hiroshima and Nagasaki (1981). <i>Hiroshima and Nagasaki: The Physical, Medical, and Social Effects of the Atomic Bombings</i>. Basic Books. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/046502985X" class="internal">ISBN 046502985X</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Hiroshima+and+Nagasaki%3A+The+Physical%2C+Medical%2C+and+Social+Effects+of+the+Atomic+Bombings&amp;rft.aulast=The+Committee+for+the+Compilation+of+Materials+on+Damage+Caused+by+the+Atomic+Bombs+in+Hiroshima+and+Nagasaki&amp;rft.au=The+Committee+for+the+Compilation+of+Materials+on+Damage+Caused+by+the+Atomic+Bombs+in+Hiroshima+and+Nagasaki&amp;rft.date=1981&amp;rft.pub=Basic+Books&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFCampbell.2C_Richard_H.2005">Campbell, Richard H. (2005). "Chapter 2: Development and Production". <i>The Silverplate Bombers: A History and Registry of the Enola Gay and Other B-29s Configured to Carry Atomic Bombs</i>. McFarland &amp; Company, Inc.. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0786421398" class="internal">ISBN 0-7864-2139-8</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Chapter+2%3A+Development+and+Production&amp;rft.atitle=The+Silverplate+Bombers%3A+A+History+and+Registry+of+the+Enola+Gay+and+Other+B-29s+Configured+to+Carry+Atomic+Bombs&amp;rft.aulast=Campbell%2C+Richard+H.&amp;rft.au=Campbell%2C+Richard+H.&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.pub=McFarland+%26+Company%2C+Inc.&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFGoldstein.2C_Donald_M.3B_Dillon.2C_Katherine_V._.26_Wenger.2C_J._Michael1995">Goldstein, Donald M; Dillon, Katherine V. &amp; Wenger, J. Michael (1995). <i>Rain of Ruin: A Photographic History of Hiroshima and Nagasaki</i>. Brasseys, Washington &amp; London. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1574880330" class="internal">ISBN 1-57488-033-0</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Rain+of+Ruin%3A+A+Photographic+History+of+Hiroshima+and+Nagasaki&amp;rft.aulast=Goldstein%2C+Donald+M%3B+Dillon%2C+Katherine+V.+%26+Wenger%2C+J.+Michael&amp;rft.au=Goldstein%2C+Donald+M%3B+Dillon%2C+Katherine+V.+%26+Wenger%2C+J.+Michael&amp;rft.date=1995&amp;rft.pub=Brasseys%2C+Washington+%26+London&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFHein.2C_Laura_and_Selden.2C_Mark_.28Editors.291997">Hein, Laura and Selden, Mark (Editors) (1997). <i>Living with the Bomb: American and Japanese Cultural Conflicts in the Nuclear Age</i>. M. E. Sharpe. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1563249679" class="internal">ISBN 1-56324-967-9</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Living+with+the+Bomb%3A+American+and+Japanese+Cultural+Conflicts+in+the+Nuclear+Age&amp;rft.aulast=Hein%2C+Laura+and+Selden%2C+Mark+%28Editors%29&amp;rft.au=Hein%2C+Laura+and+Selden%2C+Mark+%28Editors%29&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.pub=M.+E.+Sharpe&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
