<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFKnebel.2C_Fletcher_and_Bailey.2C_Charles_W.1960">Knebel, Fletcher and Bailey, Charles W. (1960). <i>No High Ground</i>. Harper and Row. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0313242216" class="internal">ISBN 0313242216</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=No+High+Ground&amp;rft.aulast=Knebel%2C+Fletcher+and+Bailey%2C+Charles+W.&amp;rft.au=Knebel%2C+Fletcher+and+Bailey%2C+Charles+W.&amp;rft.date=1960&amp;rft.pub=Harper+and+Row&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> A history of the bombings, and the decision-making to use them.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFMerton1962">Merton, Thomas (1962). <i>Original Child Bomb: Points for meditation to be scratched on the walls of a cave</i>. New Directions. ISBN B0007EVXX2 A look at the universal ramifications of this event..</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Original+Child+Bomb%3A+Points+for+meditation+to+be+scratched+on+the+walls+of+a+cave&amp;rft.aulast=Merton&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas&amp;rft.au=Merton%2C+Thomas&amp;rft.date=1962&amp;rft.pub=New+Directions&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Atomic_bombings_of_Hiroshima_and_Nagasaki"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
